Real Madrid beat Barcelona 1-0
after extra time for its first Copa del Rey soccer title since
1993.  Cristiano Ronaldo scored in the 103rd minute at the
Mestalla Stadium in Valencia to give Real Madrid its 18th
Spanish Cup title. It was Realâ€™s first victory over its rival in
six matches.  The two teams drew 1-1 in La Liga four days ago as
Barceloina maintained its eight-point lead in the standings. The
two will also meet in the semifinals of the Champions League on
